---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Next.js Directory Website Development" description="Next.js directory website development for auth, backend workflows, and dynamic directory features.">
  <section class="pt-24 pb-14">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <span class="text-sm text-[#00f0ff] font-['JetBrains_Mono'] tracking-wider">NEXT.JS BUILD</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-5 font-['Space_Grotesk']">Next.js Directory Website Development</h1>
      <p class="text-[#8b8b9a] text-lg max-w-3xl">Choose Next.js when your directory needs authentication, user workflows, or backend-driven features. Built for teams that need both SEO and product flexibility.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Best For</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Dynamic feature sets</p></div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Includes</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Auth, backend, user actions</p></div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Tradeoff</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Higher complexity vs static</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">Common Next.js directory features</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-[#c7c7d2]">
          <li>• Login/signup and protected flows</li>
          <li>• Listing claims and owner dashboards</li>
          <li>• User favorites, submissions, and moderation</li>
          <li>• API-connected dynamic directory sections</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">How scope is handled</h2>
        <p class="text-[#8b8b9a]">Dynamic features can expand quickly. I keep scope explicit: core build first, then add-ons like auth, role systems, and custom tools as structured phases.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-[#0a0a0f] bg-gradient-to-r from-[#00f0ff] to-[#00c8ff] rounded-xl">See packages + add-ons</a>
      <a href="/astro-directory-website-development" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl">Compare with Astro</a>
      <a href="mailto:tim@stackbasesystem.com" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl">Email project scope</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
